description:
&lt;p&gt;Our Bone Health Team is looking to recruit an enthusiastic and dedicated registered nurse with a particular interest in osteoporosis and its subsequent treatments such as Zoledronic acid and Denosumab.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a registered nurse with a wide range of holistic health and social care skills and experiences to complement our service. You will be working closely with GPs and the acute trust and a range of Health and Social Care Professionals where necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake initial holistic assessments and follow up visits using a range of skills. You must possess the cannulation and IV therapy competencies or be willing to undertake training to achieve these within 3 months of taking up the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is 25 hours per week.  The hours of work will be 8.30-4.30 on a rota basis but these can be negotiable. The Service operates 5 days per week Mon-Fri excluding bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your expertise and hard work, we offer a wide range of benefits including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to Agenda for Change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days annual leave plus bank holidays (This increases to 29 days after five years&#39; service and 33 days after 10 years)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lease car scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle to work scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Home electronics scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted travel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shopping discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will be required to apply for a DBS check. Nottingham CityCare Partnership is a completely smoke free organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
